<h1>Courier Express privacy policy</h1>
<div style="margin: 5px;">


<div class="small-header">The Collection and Use of Information</div>
<br />
Courier Express limits the information we collect about our partners and customers to what we need for internal business purposes only.
Courier Express understands that privacy is a critical issue for everyone and is committed to protecting personal information.
We want to earn trust by providing safeguards to protect personal information as we continue to provide valuable products and services.<br /><br />

Courier Express's Privacy Policy is designed to comply with Canada’s federal Personal Information Protection and Electronic Documents Act including the ten principles set out in the National Canadian Standards Association: Model Code for the Protection of Personal Information. Based on these guidelines and Courier Express’s Best Business Practices, ten privacy principles have been customized to meet the specific needs and expectations of our customers.<br /><br />

The Privacy Policy at Courier Express is a formal statement that outlines the minimum requirements for the protection of personal information. The objectives of the Privacy Policy are to promote responsible management of personal information, and to inform our customers of our practices.

Courier Express will continue to review this Privacy Policy to ensure it remains current with changing laws and regulations while meeting the evolving needs of customers. In the event of any amendment to the Privacy Policy, a notice will be posted within this page.<br /><br />

<div class="small-header">Privacy Statement</div>
<br />
Courier Express recognizes the importance of respecting customers’ right to privacy and adheres to the following key principles:<br /><br />

    <li>
     Courier Express is responsible for personal information under its control and has designated individuals to be accountable for the organization’s compliance.<br /><br />
    </li>
    <li>
    The  purposes for which personal information is collected will be identified at or before the time the information is collected. <br /><br />
    </li>

    <li>
    Knowledge  and consent will be obtained for the collection, use, and disclosure of personal information, except where deemed inappropriate.<br /><br />
    </li>
    <li>
    The  collection of personal information is limited to that which is related to the purposes identified by Courier Express.<br /><br />
    </li>
    <li>

    Personal information will not be used or disclosed for purposes other than those for which it was collected, except with the consent of the customer or as required by law.<br /><br />
    </li>
    <li>
    Reasonable efforts will be made to ensure that personal information is as accurate, complete, and up-to-date as is necessary for the purposes for which it is used.<br /><br />
    </li>
    <li>
    Personal information will be protected by reasonable security safeguards such as SSL certificates and strong cryptographic functions where appropriate to the sensitivity of the personal information.<br /><br />
    </li>
    <li>
    Information  is available to customers regarding Courier Express’s policies and procedures relating to the management of personal information.<br /><br />
    </li>
    <li>
    Upon request, and within a reasonable period of time, a customer will be informed of the existence, use, and disclosure of his or her personal information and will be given access to that information. A customer is entitled to comment on the accuracy and completeness of his or her personal information, and have that information amended where appropriate.<br /><br />
    </li>

    <li>
